Package com.cafean.client.values.util

Interface FunctionConstants

  • public interface FunctionConstants
    Defines a series of constants for external functions. Methods should use these keys and values when configuring a Hashtable that controls user-defined function evaluation. Each key describes the legal values that the library expects when retrieving values for the given key. Failure to use appropriate values may result in exceptions.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static java.lang.String KEY_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_BASENAME
      a key for defining the base name for a Mathcad output file: the corresponding value must be a String
      static java.lang.String KEY_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_FORMAT
      a key for defining the type of external-file exported for Mathcad functions: the corresponding value must be either VALUE_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_HTML or VALUE_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_RTF
      static java.lang.String KEY_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_LOCATION
      a key for defining the location of Mathcad output files: the corresponding value must be a File
      static java.lang.String VALUE_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_HTML
      a value for exporting HTML documents to detail the contents of a Mathcad file
      static java.lang.String VALUE_MATHCAD_OUTPUT_RTF
      a value for exporting rich-text format documents to detail the contents of a Mathcad file
